# Interview Explanation

### Question

Why Binary Search?

### Answer

Because:

```
f(k) = 1² + 2² + ... + k²
```

is strictly increasing.

If:

```
f(k) ≤ p
```

then all smaller values are also valid.

If:

```
f(k) > p
```

then all larger values are invalid.

This creates a monotonic search space, making Binary Search applicable.

